          "message_id": "3b5e2baf-2451-4776-bfe4-97c72b6c6ba6",
          "content": "It's the **difference** between what the OS reports as total network traffic (`psutil.net_io_counters`) and what scapy actually captured per-process.\n\nThat gap happens because:\n\n- **VPNs** — encrypt and tunnel traffic, so scapy sees the tunnel packets but can't attribute them to the real app\n- **System-level traffic** — Windows kernel, NDIS drivers, DNS, DHCP, NetBIOS, Windows Update running at a low level before packets reach the point scapy hooks\n- **Loopback/virtual adapters** — traffic on `127.0.0.1` or virtual interfaces that scapy isn't sniffing on the selected adapter\n- **Missed packets** — if scapy drops packets under high load, those bytes show up in the OS counter but not in any process bucket\n\nSo it's essentially **\"traffic the OS moved but scapy couldn't attribute to a PID\"**."
        }
